<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>How does an inflationary gap affect the price level over time?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The price level gradually falls until the gap closes</option>
            <option letter="b">The price level remains constant despite the gap</option>
            <option letter="c">The price level gradually rises until the gap closes</option>
            <option letter="d">The price level falls then rises cyclically</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>In an inflationary gap, where actual GDP exceeds potential GDP, upward pressure on wages and prices occurs. The price level gradually rises over time as this excess demand pushes up costs, eventually bringing actual GDP back to potential GDP level.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
